                  >DTI Ratio</a
                >
                tools automate these checks for you.
              </p>

              <h2>Choosing the right mortgage type</h2>
              <p>
                Different loan programs suit different buyers. Use the
                calculators in this hub to compare:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Conventional loans</strong> – often best for strong
                  credit and larger down payments.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>FHA loans</strong> – lower down payment and more
                  flexible credit, but include mortgage insurance.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>VA loans</strong> – for eligible veterans and service
                  members, often with no down payment.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Adjustable‑rate mortgages (ARMs)</strong> – lower
                  initial rate, but rate can change later.
                </li>
              </ul>

